## OpenAI Build Week — Codex + GPT-5.6

SideShift was significantly extended during OpenAI Build Week using OpenAI Codex powered by GPT-5.6.

Codex and GPT-5.6 helped me:

- navigate and understand the full React and TypeScript codebase;
- implement structured multi-turn AI debates;
- build Supabase authentication, Row Level Security, and secure database flows;
- diagnose Android, Capacitor, WebView, API-routing, and logout issues;
- create Friends, Groups, Team Debate, World Pulse, and private leagues;
- improve multilingual support across English, German, French, Spanish, and Italian;
- add and verify 125 automated tests;
- build and test the Android APK.

I remained responsible for the SideSwitch concept, product direction, privacy model, visual design, feature decisions, safety constraints, and final acceptance of each implementation.

The repository’s commit history documents the Build Week development work.
